  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Environmental participatory management and implementing environmental alternatives, Espinar, Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will work with indigenous campesino communities in the Espinar region of Peru, specifically in Yauri district and across the Ca&#xF1;ipia and Salado de Espinar basins. This project continues previous CAFOD advocacy support to generate environmental policies in Espinar and development alternatives across both watersheds. This project also prioritises institutional strengthening through coordinated interventions with strategic allies. The main project participants are the community leaders, environmental defenders and promoters who will receive advocacy training in generating environmental policies. The project will include exchanges with other communities on alternative development and support the production of community proposals for development alternatives that contribute to household income and local economies.</narrative>
  </description>
